title: H1N1 Virus Hospitalizations, ICU and Fatal Cases in CA by Local Health Jurisdiction, as of 09/26/09
name: H1N1 Virus Hospitalizations, ICU and Fatal Cases in CA by Local Health Jurisdiction, as of 09/26/09
description:
This is a shapefile of hospitalizations, icu and fatal cases from H1N1 in California by county. Uploaded as shp, dbf, and shx files. 

The reported number of cases of novel influenza A (H1N1) virus in California do not reflect how many actual cases there may be in the state because individuals in outpatient settings are no longer being tested for the presence of the virus and many cases go undetected due to the mild nature of disease among most people.  Laboratory testing is limited to individuals with serious H1N1 illness, including hospitalized patients, and those at high risk for complications.   

Local Health Jurisdictions include the 58 county health departments and 3 city health departments (Berkeley, Long Beach, and Pasadena).  The city health departments are not included in the county totals.
